{"favorite_id": 2200, "calc_type": "", "dosing": false, "full_title_en": "Fibrosis-4 (FIB-4) Index for Liver Fibrosis", "short_title_en": "FIB-4 Index", "medium_description_en": "Noninvasive estimate of liver scarring in HCV and HBV patients, to assess need for biopsy.", "short_description_en": "Noninvasive estimate of liver fibrosis.", "before_use": "", "instructions_en": "", "purpose_en": ["Diagnosis"], "disease_en": ["Cirrhosis", "HIV/AIDS", "Hepatitis"], "specialty_en": ["Gastroenterology", "Hepatology", "Infectious Disease", "Internal Medicine", "Primary Care"], "chief_complaint_en": ["AMS", "Abdominal Pain", "Agitation", "Weakness"], "system_en": ["Gastrointestinal", "Infectious"], "search_abbreviation_en": ["fibrosis", "cirrhosis", "fib", "fib4", "fib-4", "hepatic", "calculation", "hepatitis", "HCV", "HIV", "fib 4"], "slug": "fibrosis-4-fib-4-index-liver-fibrosis", "seo": {"meta_description_en": "The Fibrosis-4 (FIB-4) Index for Liver Fibrosis is a non-invasive scoring system based on several laboratory tests that help to estimate the amount of scarring in the liver.", "keywords_en": "fib-4, fibrosis 4 score, fib-4 score, fib 4"}, "content": {"how_to_use": {"use_case_en": "<ul> <li>Patients with any known risk factors for liver disease, including chronic hepatitis, alcoholic liver disease, <calculator id=\"3081\">non-alcoholic fatty liver disease (NAFLD)</calculator> and the cholestatic and metabolic liver diseases.</li> <li>Patients with known liver fibrosis should have their fibrosis trended over time to evaluate for progression or stabilization.</li> </ul>", "pearls_pitfalls_en": "<ul> <li>Liver fibrosis often progresses non-linearly, so it is important to be able to re-assess fibrosis trends in individual patients over time, and invasive re-assessments carry significant risk to patients. FIB-4 allows for non-invasive liver fibrosis assessment.</li> <li>FIB-4 was developed in patients with HIV and HCV co-infection.</li> <li>FIB-4 was developed to correlate with Ishak levels of fibrosis (by biopsy) with 3 levels: <ul> <li>0-2 (mild fibrosis)</li> <li>3-4 (moderate fibrosis)</li> <li>5-6 (severe fibrosis/cirrhosis)</li> </ul> </li> </ul>", "why_use_en": "<ul> <li>While liver biopsy is the gold standard for the diagnosis of liver fibrosis, it is not ideal; biopsy only evaluates a minute portion of the liver itself, so sampling errors can occur. Liver biopsy also comes with substantial morbidity.</li> <li>Liver fibrosis often progresses non-linearly, so it is important to be able to re-assess fibrosis trends in individual patients over time.</li> <li>It is critical that tests to identify liver cirrhosis are highly sensitive, as patients with the disease require screening for hepatocellular carcinoma (HCC) and gastroesophageal varices.</li> <li>The FIB-4 Index was shown to be superior to 7 other noninvasive markers of fibrosis in patients with NAFLD, including the <calculator id='3081'>NAFLD Fibrosis Score</calculator> (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19523535\" target=\"_blank\">Shah 2009</a>).</li> </ul>"}, "next_steps": {"advice_en": "<ul> <li>Low fibrosis scores may be appropriate candidates for medical management and may not require liver biopsy if FIB-4 scores continue to stay low.</li> <li>Severe fibrosis/cirrhosis scores may need liver biopsy for confirmation of cirrhosis unless there are other clinical or imaging signs of progression to end-stage liver disease.</li> </ul>", "management_en": "", "critical_actions_en": ""}, "about": {"formula_en": "<p>FIB-4 Score = (Age* x AST) / (Platelets x &radic;(ALT))</p>\n<p>*Use with caution in patients &lt;35&nbsp;or &gt;65&nbsp;years old, as the score has been shown to be less reliable in these patients.</p>", "more_info_en": "<p>Interpretation:</p>\n<p><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" xmlns:xlink=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\" version=\"1.1\" width=\"100%\" height=\"auto\" viewbox=\"-0.5 -0.5 584 425\" content=\"&lt;mxfile modified=&quot;2019-07-30T18:51:39.137Z&quot; host=&quot;www.draw.io&quot; agent=&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_13_3) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/75.0.3770.100 Safari/537.36&quot; version=&quot;11.0.7&quot; etag=&quot;xH3RS-X1DfuL5ixSjxIf&quot; type=&quot;google&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram id=&quot;-YXkpV8V8MC0a9oHEGLq&quot;&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;\"><defs></defs><g><g transform=\"translate(201.5,2.5)\"><switch><foreignobject style=\"overflow: visible;\" pointer-events=\"all\" width=\"189\" height=\"14\" requiredfeatures=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/feature#Extensibility\">\n<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-size: 14px; font-family: Facit; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; white-space: nowrap; font-weight: bold; text-align: center;\">\n<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" style=\"display: inline-block; text-align: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;\">Age specific use of FIB-4 Score</div>\n</div>\n</foreignobject><text x=\"95\" y=\"14\" fill=\"#000000\" text-anchor=\"middle\" font-size=\"14px\" font-family=\"Facit\" font-weight=\"bold\">Age specific use of FIB-4 Score</text></switch></g><rect x=\"4\" y=\"353\" width=\"115\" height=\"70\" fill=\"#d5d5d5\" stroke=\"#1ec2a1\" stroke-width=\"2\" pointer-events=\"none\"></rect><g transform=\"translate(5.5,374.5)\"><switch><foreignobject style=\"overflow: visible;\" pointer-events=\"all\" width=\"111\" height=\"25\" requiredfeatures=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/feature#Extensibility\">\n<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" style=\"display: inline-block; font-size: 12px; font-family: Facit; color: #000000; line-height: 1.2; vertical-align: top; width: 110px; white-space: nowrap; overflow-wrap: normal; text-align: center;\">\n<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" style=\"display: inline-block; text-align: inherit; text-decoration: inherit; white-space: normal;\">Alternative fibrosis assessment</div>\n</div>\n</foreignobject>